args: Sir Raemond?! So you're here, too.
Indeed I am. I was off guarding the fort,\nbut the moment I heard you were here at\nthe castle, I came running.
You seem different. Are you eating well?

A knight must always keep themselves in
good health. If you cannot swing the sword
upon which you swore fealty to the king,
you lose the right to call yourself a knight.
Hnkh! Nnngh... Sir Raemond,\nplease forgive this indiscretion!
Are you mad, child?! How is eating rocks\ngoing to help you?!
This isn't just some regular old rock!\nIt's the best rock EVER!

Just as I thought... Well, nevertheless!
I am not the kind of man who can overlook
his former subordinate shattering her teeth
on random pebbles.
Hand it over, Cecile. And I'll also have you\nspit out what you just ate.
No! I won't ever let anyone have it!\nNot even you, Sir Raemond!
You're just as stubborn as always.\nWell, two can play at that—
How could this have happened to two of\nthe former king's most honored knights?
I'm so sorry, Leif. Er, and thanks for\ntreating Sir Raemond for me.
I'll repay you on the battlefield.
Or you could just give me a discount on\nyour sellsword services.
Let's not get crazy now. I still have my\npride as a mercenary.
...Lately you seem to have come to\naccept your position of being here as\na mercenary.
Before, you said you wanted to regain your\noptimism so you could again be a knight...
Yeah, well, I think I'm done trying to be\nlike my old self.
Then you're giving up on knighthood?
No, I'm still considering that. But I'm done\ntrying to regain my old shine.
Living life openly and positively is great,\nbut after countless attempts, I've realized\nthat I just can't do it anymore.
Yes—and I'm also fine with it. After all,\nI'm only giving up on the optimism part.
My old self was forthright and positive,\nwhich I always thought of as a strength.
But now I think it was a kind of weakness;\nmy obsession with pursuing my ideals was\nactually what made me so easy to break.

And yeah, I'm still pretty broken—and full
of plenty of new weaknesses—but I also
have a new kind of strength that will keep
me from ever breaking down again.
A shattered sword cannot be broken anew.\nThis will be how I live from now on.
Your words stir my very soul, Cecile.
They shouldn't. And look, I can't pretend I\ndon't still long for the days when I used to\nwork tirelessly toward my ideals.
But I need to learn how to accept myself\nas I am now before I do anything else.
Seeing as you are perfectly dependable as\nyou are, I believe that is for the best.
Thank you, Captain Leif. And once again,\nthis mercenary is at your service.
I am glad to have you, Lady Cecile.
And I'M just happy we all finally get\nto fight together!
I will give my all at every moment on the\nbattlefield so I might keep up with Cecile.
My pride as a White Sparrow is at stake!

I'm okay the way I am—and coming to grips with
that is how I'll be able to stay here.

But...
I still melt in the radiance of other people.
